description:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POST 1: 16.5 hours per week, permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POST 2: 21 hours per week, fixed term or secondment until 31/03/2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting a highly motivated Domestic Assistant (Band 2) at Whitchurch Community Hospital to carry out domestic duties and help us maintain the high standards already set within this department.    &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder would cover duties which would mainly include the cleaning of clinical areas, both on the wards and in our outpatient areas along with administration offices plus other hospital departments. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are various times and lengths of shifts available starting from 7.30 am – 7.00 pm providing a 7 day service, including weekends and bank holidays on a rota to meet the needs of this service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For post 2, additional hours would be available if so desired and following the end of this fixed term contract we would look at the opportunity of encouraging the individual to stay within our team where possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As our team provides a service from 7.00 am to 7.00 pm everyday there would also be an opportunity and the flexibility to do extra shifts, especially to assist with cover for annual leave etc.   &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full training will be given.    &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for individuals who are organised and able to work effectively alone or as part of a team with high standards.  There will be an opportunity to discuss flexibility and hours at interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;AS A MANDATORY PART OF THE RECRUITMENT PROCESS YOU SHOULD ANSWER THE FOLLOWING QUESTION IN YOUR SUPPORTING STATEMENT &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;(MAXIMUM OF 100 WORDS):&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‘why you think respect is important when working within in a team’&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
